# Configuration

**All numeric parameters live in one file:** `toxic_game.toml` at the repo root. No magic numbers in code — read from config.

Per-song data (BPM, delay, audio path, name) lives in `songs/<song_id>/song.toml`. Tap notes are separate text files in the same folder.

## `toxic_game.toml` (global)

```toml
[paths]
songs_dir = "songs"

[gpio]
left_contact_pin = 17
right_contact_pin = 27

[led]
muted_rgb_count = 20   # n: leading RGB LEDs (always off)
rgbw_count = 60        # m: active RGBW gameplay LEDs
pin = 18
freq_hz = 800000
dma = 10
invert = false
brightness = 255
channel = 0
hit_flash_ms = 180        # white/red flash duration at strip end
running_light_span = 4    # LEDs per traveling note (prototype default)

[gameplay]
lead_time_beats = 4       # running light spawns 1 bar (4 beats) before hit

[gameplay.judgement_windows_ms]
perfect = 20              # ±20 ms from beat
good = 50                 # ±50 ms from beat (must be >= perfect)

[gameplay.health]
start = 20
max = 20                  # cap regen at start value
lose_on_error = 2
gain_on_good = 1
gain_on_perfect = 2

[runtime]
update_hz = 60            # game loop target rate
```

## Assumptions (change in config if needed)

- Judgement: **perfect** is the tighter window (20 ms); **good** is wider (50 ms)
- Health regen cannot exceed `max` (= `start`)
- Ghost taps (press with no active note) are ignored — no health change
- GPIO/LED defaults match `/home/pi/rythm-jump/rythm_jump.toml` until hardware differs

## `songs/<song_id>/song.toml` (per song)

```toml
name = "Song Title"
audio = "audio.mp3"
bpm = 120.0
delay_to_first_beat_ms = 0
```

## Tap note files (per song)

- `p1.taps` — Player 1 (left), one `bar.beat` per line (1-based)
- `p2.taps` — Player 2 (right), same format
- Quantize to nearest quarter note when recording
